{"parentUuid": "8c154975-f1e7-4555-9f04-31284cad63ad", "isSidechain": false, "userType": "external", "cwd": "/Users/josephgenest/Desktop/MercorSprint31926/model_a", "sessionId": "378ffb02-262f-4011-aa1a-391157ff695e", "version": "2.1.70", "gitBranch": "main", "type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "We are building a paywalled blog using Stripe, Sanity, and ThirdWeb. First, we need to establish a CMS with Sanity that has a schema with the following features: Authors (author page), posts, and premium content switch (for paywall). For our Stripe payment, we\u2019d like to make it a smooth pop-up with Google/Apple Pay and all our branding (Futura Titles + Helvetica body). Ideally, the pop-up should rest on the paywall like you\u2019d see out of the New York Times, Washington Post, etc. We\u2019re going to use ThirdWeb for two things: first, I like their social sign in button for using a wallet, so we\u2019re going to use that. The second thing will be ThirdWeb\u2019s ability to mint a simple smart contract that mints our membership.\n\nLet\u2019s create a demo page at /demo with placeholder text, the paywall over top, the sign in option with ThirdWeb, and our Stripe pop-up with Google/Apple Pay. We\u2019re going to enter Env Vars last, so let\u2019s have a working demo as the priority to ensure everything is set up correctly, then refactor in the smart contract + Env Vars.\n"}, "uuid": "67f26435-9074-4db9-add2-6f72733855f5", "timestamp": "2026-03-19T14:57:32.875Z", "permissionMode": "default", "task_id": "TASK_14973", "model_lane": "model_a", "experiment_root": "/Users/josephgenest/Desktop/MercorSprint31926", "model_name": "claude-strudel-v6-p"}
